       A Different Kind of Smart
       Zola the crow is about to face a test that has baffled animals from canaries to dogs.
       She's a wild New Caledonian crow, and for the first time, she's seeing a tidbit of meat dangling on a long string tied to a stick. She perches on the stick, bends down, grabs the string
       with her beak and pulls. But the string is too long. The meat still hangs out of reach. 04.18.13 | more >>
       Mick Sibley/Univ. of Auckland
