       Quakes in Slo-Mo
       Herb Dragert didn't know what to make of his wayward station.
       In the early days of GPS satellites, Dragert had set up four benchmarks in the bedrock of Vancouver Island, British Columbia, to watch how their positions changed over time. Maybe, he
       thought, he could capture the ground moving during the earthquakes that occasionally shake the Pacific Northwest. 03.07.13 | more >>
       Pacific Northwest Geodetic Array/Central Washington Univ.
