       Of Mice and Man
       It looked like a lost cause: a 61-year-old patient with advanced pancreatic cancer -- one of the deadliest diagnoses. Ordinarily, doctors wouldn't have much choice. They could try
       chemotherapy drugs one at a time to see if any worked, or they could slam the tumor with a cocktail of chemicals that had shown some success with similar cases. 03.07.13 | more >>
